♪ NEVER YOU FEAR

01:35.530 --> 01:37.488
♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR

01:37.619 --> 01:41.013
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:41.144 --> 01:44.060
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

02:01.817 --> 02:03.210
-[SIRENS BLARING]

02:10.173 --> 02:14.699
-[EXCITING MUSIC]

02:24.318 --> 02:25.623
-GARNER, CALL AN AMBULANCE!

02:25.754 --> 02:26.711
-GARNER: ALL RIGHT!

03:16.326 --> 03:17.371
-HOBIE!

03:18.415 --> 03:19.242
-DAD!

03:19.373 --> 03:20.548
DAD!

03:20.678 --> 03:22.202
DAD, OVER HERE!
I CAN'T FIND HER!

03:22.332 --> 03:23.464
-GET HOBIE.
-ALL RIGHT.

03:32.124 --> 03:33.561
-ALL RIGHT, TAKE THE CAN, HOBE.

03:35.432 --> 03:40.350
-[TENSE MUSIC]

04:23.698 --> 04:24.699
-MITCH: LET'S GET HER IN.

04:27.049 --> 04:28.180
-LET'S GO.

04:35.318 --> 04:36.232
GOT IT?

04:36.363 --> 04:37.277
-YEAH, I'M FINE.

04:49.506 --> 04:51.291
-MITCH: NO PULSE.

04:51.421 --> 04:54.337
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

04:55.120 --> 04:56.992
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

04:58.515 --> 05:00.561
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

05:00.691 --> 05:02.780
-COME ON!
-MITCH: COME ON, JOEY!

05:02.911 --> 05:04.652
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

05:07.568 --> 05:08.960
[COUGHING]

05:09.091 --> 05:09.831
-MITCH: OKAY, COME ON, COME ON.
PULL HER UP.

05:09.961 --> 05:10.701
THAT'S A GIRL.

05:10.832 --> 05:12.181
OKAY.

05:12.312 --> 05:13.704
ALL RIGHT.

05:25.237 --> 05:26.630
-IT'S THE SAME GUY
THAT CHASED JOEY

05:26.761 --> 05:27.979
UNDER THE PIER YESTERDAY.

05:28.110 --> 05:29.329
I HAD TO CLIMB UP AFTER HER.

05:29.459 --> 05:30.852
I COULDN'T LEAVE HER ALONE.

05:30.982 --> 05:32.244
-AND YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT HE WAS AFTER?

05:33.724 --> 05:35.073
I'M GONNA HAVE YOU
GIVE OUR POLICE ARTIST

05:35.204 --> 05:36.597
A DESCRIPTION FOR A COMPOSITE

05:36.727 --> 05:38.163
AND WE'LL HAVE YOU LOOK
AT SOME MUGSHOTS, OKAY?

05:38.294 --> 05:39.904
-OKAY.

05:40.035 --> 05:41.863
-I'M PROUD OF THE WAY YOU
HANDLED YOURSELF, HOBIE.

05:41.993 --> 05:44.300
YOU'RE GONNA BE A FIRST-RATE
LIFEGUARD, JUST LIKE YOUR DAD.

05:44.431 --> 05:46.911
-AND I'M SURE MRS. JENNINGS
WILL THANK YOU PERSONALLY,

05:47.042 --> 05:48.348
IF SHE EVER SHOWS UP.

05:49.523 --> 05:50.567
-MRS. JENNINGS.

05:52.090 --> 05:53.483
KYLA JENNINGS?

05:53.614 --> 05:55.224
-YEAH, YEAH, I THINK SO.

05:55.355 --> 05:56.747
JOEY'S MOTHER, YOU KNOW HER?

05:56.878 --> 05:58.662
-I ARRESTED A KYLA JENNINGS
TWO DAYS AGO.

05:58.793 --> 06:01.099
SHE'S UH, DOWN AT THE COUNTY
JAIL WAITING TO BE BAILED OUT.

06:03.319 --> 06:04.712
-WELL, WHAT DID
YOU ARREST HER FOR?

06:04.842 --> 06:06.409
-SHE'S A-- A CON WOMAN.

06:06.540 --> 06:08.890
SHE AND A LITTLE BOY
CONNED A BOARDWALK VENDOR

06:09.020 --> 06:10.413
OUT OF $100.

06:11.588 --> 06:13.155
-I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

06:13.285 --> 06:16.245
-YEAH, GARNER, THAT LITTLE
BOY IS A LITTLE GIRL.

06:17.551 --> 06:20.380
AND I THINK IT'S TIME I HAVE A
HEART TO HEART TALK WITH HER.

06:20.510 --> 06:21.642
EXCUSE ME.

06:27.952 --> 06:29.171
[KNOCKING]

06:29.301 --> 06:30.172
-COME IN.

06:32.348 --> 06:33.741
-HEY.

06:33.871 --> 06:34.872
[SIGHING]

06:35.003 --> 06:36.396
HEY.

06:38.963 --> 06:40.312
I BROUGHT YOU A LITTLE
SANDWICH HERE, HUH,

06:40.443 --> 06:41.618
IN CASE YOU GET HUNGRY.

06:42.358 --> 06:43.228
-THANKS.

06:44.447 --> 06:46.275
IT WAS NICE OF YOU TO
LET ME USE YOUR ROOM.

06:46.406 --> 06:48.146
-IT'S OKAY.

06:48.277 --> 06:50.497
THAT WAS SOME SWAN DIVE
YOU TOOK OFF THE PIER, HUH?

06:50.627 --> 06:52.150
[LAUGHING]

06:53.238 --> 06:54.239
-THANKS FOR SAVING ME.

06:54.370 --> 06:56.154
-THAT'S OKAY, YOU'RE WELCOME.

06:58.896 --> 07:00.550
YOU KNOW, JOEY, UM...

07:01.812 --> 07:03.074
I KNOW ABOUT YOUR MOM.

07:03.205 --> 07:04.598
-MY MOM'LL BE HERE TOMORROW.

07:04.728 --> 07:05.947
I KNOW SHE WILL.

07:06.077 --> 07:07.862
-I KNOW SHE'S IN JAIL.

07:09.472 --> 07:10.517
-BUT I'M GONNA BAIL HER OUT.

07:11.648 --> 07:12.649
-WITH WHAT?

07:12.780 --> 07:13.824
-WE'LL BE FINE.

07:13.955 --> 07:15.043
HONEST.

07:16.131 --> 07:17.088
-YOU KNOW...

07:18.916 --> 07:20.570
I'M A LIFEGUARD, RIGHT?

07:20.701 --> 07:24.182
AND IT'S MY JOB TO KNOW
WHEN SOMEONE'S IN TROUBLE

07:24.313 --> 07:25.183
AND NEEDS HELP.

07:30.232 --> 07:31.799
-MY MOM AND I LIVE
OFF THE STREETS.

07:32.452 --> 07:34.932
WE'RE HOMELESS UNLESS WE HAVE
ENOUGH MONEY FOR A MOTEL.

07:35.803 --> 07:37.544
I WAS SUPPOSED TO BAIL HER OUT,

07:37.674 --> 07:38.849
BUT I LOST THE MONEY.

07:39.459 --> 07:40.808
NOW SHE DOESN'T KNOW WHERE I AM

07:40.938 --> 07:42.679
AND WHY I HAVEN'T COME FOR HER.

07:44.855 --> 07:46.683
-[SIGHING]

07:50.644 --> 07:52.210
IF THERE REALLY WAS A SANTA,

07:52.341 --> 07:54.343
HE'D BRING MY MOM
BACK FOR CHRISTMAS.

07:58.303 --> 07:59.348
-I TELL YOU WHAT.

08:00.175 --> 08:01.655
IF YOU EAT SOME
OF THIS SANDWICH,

08:01.785 --> 08:04.571
THEN I PERSONALLY
WILL CALL SANTA CLAUS

08:05.136 --> 08:06.834
AND SEE IF HE'LL
GRANT YOUR REQUEST.

08:17.584 --> 08:18.585
EAT.

08:20.064 --> 08:20.891
-WOULD YOU LIKE SOME?

08:21.022 --> 08:22.458
-NO, NO NO.

08:22.589 --> 08:23.720
YOU EAT FIRST, I'LL
GET SOME LATER, OKAY?

08:27.202 --> 08:29.378
-MY MOM ALWAYS LET
ME EAT FIRST, TOO.

08:30.858 --> 08:33.077
THAT'S WHEN YOU KNOW HOW
SOMEONE CARES ABOUT YOU.

08:33.600 --> 08:34.775
THEY LET YOU EAT FIRST.

08:36.515 --> 08:38.039
AND THERE'S ANOTHER WAY, TOO.

08:39.039 --> 08:40.998
WHEN SOMEONE SAVES YOUR LIFE.

08:41.129 --> 08:42.696
LIKE YOU AND HOBIE DID TO ME.

08:44.349 --> 08:45.394
THANKS, MITCH.

08:50.747 --> 08:52.009
-YOU'RE WELCOME.

08:52.140 --> 08:53.576
GOT A LITTLE MUSTARD THERE, HUH?

08:53.707 --> 08:55.099
NOW EAT.

09:12.552 --> 09:15.032
[GROANING]

09:15.163 --> 09:16.468
SMOKE.

09:19.210 --> 09:20.690
[GROANING]

09:20.821 --> 09:22.474
[SNIFFING]

09:22.605 --> 09:23.780
WHA--?

09:25.608 --> 09:27.001
WHAT IS THIS? WHA--?

09:27.131 --> 09:29.090
YOU ARE SMOKING A CIGARETTE?

09:29.220 --> 09:30.874
WHAT IS THE STORY HERE?

09:31.005 --> 09:32.136
-I COULDN'T SLEEP.

09:32.267 --> 09:33.834
STRANGE BED AND ALL.

09:33.964 --> 09:35.792
-YOU HAD NO PROBLEM
SLEEPING LAST NIGHT.

09:36.401 --> 09:37.185
-THAT WAS THEN.

09:37.315 --> 09:38.273
THIS IS NOW.

09:39.143 --> 09:40.014
-LISTEN, YOUNG LADY.

09:40.144 --> 09:41.885
SMOKING IS NOT COOL.

09:42.016 --> 09:43.713
NOW, IF YOU HAVE A
PROBLEM FALLING ASLEEP,

09:43.844 --> 09:45.280
YOU SHOULD FIND
SOMETHING ELSE TO DO.

09:45.410 --> 09:46.716
-WELL THEN I'LL READ.

09:47.935 --> 09:48.979
-THIS IS THE RACING FORM.

09:49.110 --> 09:50.328
COME ON, IN THE BED.

09:52.287 --> 09:54.594
COME ON, SLIDE DOWN, IN, IN.

10:00.338 --> 10:01.165
WHAT IS THIS?

10:01.296 --> 10:02.297
-IN CASE I GET HUNGRY.

10:02.427 --> 10:03.385
-GIVE ME THOSE.

10:05.735 --> 10:06.693
I'LL TRADE YOU.

10:09.173 --> 10:10.479
GOODNIGHT.

10:27.061 --> 10:28.018
-HEY.

10:28.149 --> 10:29.324
MITCH, KYLA JENNINGS.

10:29.454 --> 10:31.108
KYLA, THE MAN WHO
BAILED YOU OUT.

10:31.718 --> 10:33.067
-SERGEANT ELLERBEE TOLD
ME EVERYTHING YOU DID

10:33.197 --> 10:35.460
FOR MY DAUGHTER,
INCLUDING SAVING HER LIFE.

10:35.591 --> 10:38.202
AND I'D STILL BE SITTING IN
JAIL IF IT WASN'T FOR YOU.

10:38.855 --> 10:39.943
I GUESS WE BOTH
OWE YOU OUR LIVES.

10:40.074 --> 10:41.728
-THE GENTLEMAN YOU BOTH CONNED

10:41.858 --> 10:43.555
HAS AGREED TO DROP THE CHARGES

10:43.686 --> 10:45.122
AS LONG AS YOU GIVE
BACK THE MONEY,

10:45.253 --> 10:46.646
BUT THE JUDGE WANTS
TO TALK TO YOU.

10:46.776 --> 10:48.125
HE WANTS TO TALK TO BOTH OF YOU.

10:48.256 --> 10:49.823
-WHAT CAN I SAY BUT THANK YOU.

10:49.953 --> 10:53.130
-MOM! MOM! MOM! MOM!

10:53.261 --> 10:54.958
-OH, THANK GOD YOU'RE OKAY!

10:55.089 --> 10:56.394
-HOW'D YOU GET HERE?

10:56.525 --> 10:57.569
-MITCH.

10:58.701 --> 10:59.659
-MITCH.

11:00.224 --> 11:01.225
-YEAH.

11:02.836 --> 11:06.274
-I STILL DON'T BELIEVE IN
SANTA, BUT I BELIEVE IN YOU.

11:06.927 --> 11:08.189
-AH.

11:19.853 --> 11:21.245
-CAROLINE: JOHN, IT'S
LOOKING REALLY GOOD.

11:21.376 --> 11:22.594
-JOHN: IT SURE IS.

11:23.726 --> 11:25.119
-JOEY, I DON'T UNDERSTAND

11:25.249 --> 11:27.077
WHAT THIS HAS TO DO WITH
HOW YOU LOST THE MONEY.

11:27.208 --> 11:29.036
-SEE ALL THOSE
PRESENTS WRAPPED ALIKE?

11:29.166 --> 11:30.341
-CARLA: YEAH.

11:30.472 --> 11:31.908
-WELL, THE MONEY'S
IN ONE OF THOSE.

11:33.997 --> 11:35.564
DON'T ASK, MOM.

11:35.695 --> 11:37.348
ALL I KNOW IS, WE'VE GOTTA
WAIT UNTIL CHRISTMAS.

11:37.479 --> 11:38.349
-OH NO.

11:43.311 --> 11:44.399
COME ON.

11:52.929 --> 11:55.149
-C.J., YOU KNOW
BENNY AND HIS FRIENDS?

11:55.279 --> 11:57.978
-YEAH.
-THE GUYS HAVE BEEN
HANGING AROUND MY TOWER.

11:58.108 --> 11:59.980
HAVE YOU NOTICED ANYTHING
DIFFERENT ABOUT THEM?

12:00.763 --> 12:02.852
-YEAH, WELL THEY'RE
NOT TOO TALL.

12:02.983 --> 12:05.159
-WELL, ACTUALLY
THAT'S PART OF IT.

12:05.289 --> 12:07.596
THEY SAY THEY'RE FROM
THIS REALLY COLD PLACE,

12:07.727 --> 12:09.032
AND THEY WORK FOR THE GUY

12:09.163 --> 12:11.339
WHO'S REALLY OLD AND
HIS NAME IS KRIS.

12:11.469 --> 12:13.471
BENNY SAID THAT IF HE
TOLD ME WHAT THEY DID,

12:13.602 --> 12:15.212
I WOULDN'T BELIEVE HIM.

12:15.343 --> 12:17.998
AND DEBBIE IS ALWAYS
TRYING TO SHUT HIM UP.

12:18.999 --> 12:20.391
I CAME TO MY TOWER
THE OTHER DAY,

12:20.957 --> 12:22.829
AND THE WHOLE THING
WAS DECORATED.

12:22.959 --> 12:24.221
CHRISTMAS TREE INSIDE,

12:24.352 --> 12:26.180
A STOCKING WITH MY NAME ON IT.

12:26.310 --> 12:28.182
BENNY AND THE GANG WENT
IN THERE ONE MINUTE

12:28.312 --> 12:29.531
AND OUT THE NEXT.

12:29.661 --> 12:31.402
I MEAN, THIS IS
JUST ALL TOO WEIRD.

12:31.533 --> 12:33.100
-WELL, IT DOESN'T
SEEM WEIRD TO ME.

12:33.230 --> 12:34.928
THAT'S PERFECTLY LOGICAL.

12:36.407 --> 12:37.626
THEY'RE ELVES.

12:38.322 --> 12:39.193
-SANTA'S ELVES?

12:39.323 --> 12:40.150
-SURE!

12:40.281 --> 12:41.195
IT MAKES PERFECT SENSE.

12:41.325 --> 12:42.762
THEY KNOW THAT AS A CHILD,

12:42.892 --> 12:44.415
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TOO
MANY HAPPY CHRISTMASES,

12:44.546 --> 12:47.027
SO THAT'S WHAT THEY'RE
GIVING YOU NOW FOR CHRISTMAS.

12:48.028 --> 12:49.464
-AND YOU BELIEVE
ALL THIS, DON'T YOU?

12:49.594 --> 12:50.682
-WELL, IF THERE CAN BE ALIENS,

12:50.813 --> 12:51.945
WHY CAN'T THERE BE ELVES?

12:52.684 --> 12:53.729
-AH.

12:54.382 --> 12:56.384
C.J., YOU'VE BEEN A BIG HELP.

12:56.514 --> 12:57.777
NOW I KNOW WHAT TO
GET YOU FOR CHRISTMAS.

12:57.907 --> 12:58.865
-REALLY? WHAT?

12:58.995 --> 13:00.605
-SOMETHING IN WHITE CANVAS,

13:00.736 --> 13:03.391
HAS LONG SLEEVES AND
TIES IN THE BACK.

13:04.827 --> 13:05.959
-MATT: COME ON!
-C.J.: MATT!

13:06.089 --> 13:07.047
-[LAUGHING]

13:07.177 --> 13:08.875
-GET BACK HERE!

13:09.005 --> 13:10.790
[LAUGHING]

13:17.274 --> 13:18.623
-HEY GUYS, COME ON IN.

13:24.978 --> 13:26.501
-UH, DAD...

13:27.197 --> 13:30.026
WE KINDA HAVE TO TALK
TO YOU FOR A SECOND.

13:31.027 --> 13:31.985
-OH NO.

13:32.115 --> 13:33.682
WHEN YOU KINDA NEED TO TALK,

13:33.813 --> 13:35.205
I KNOW THAT
SOMETHING'S COMING UP

13:35.336 --> 13:36.641
THAT I'M KINDA NOT GONNA LIKE.

13:39.340 --> 13:40.210
HIT ME.

13:40.341 --> 13:41.821
-JOEY AND I, WE--

13:41.951 --> 13:43.300
-MITCH?

13:43.431 --> 13:44.649
EXCUSE ME.

13:44.780 --> 13:46.477
I THINK YOU BETTER GET OUT HERE.

13:56.574 --> 14:00.752
-[CHATTERING]

14:00.883 --> 14:02.711
SO, THESE LOVELY LADIES
SAY THEY'RE ALL HERE

14:02.842 --> 14:04.365
WAITING FOR YOU TO CHOOSE.

14:05.932 --> 14:07.324
-CHOOSE WHAT?

14:09.196 --> 14:11.024
-THEY SOLD US
CHANCES TO BE CHOSEN

14:11.154 --> 14:12.764
TO RIDE IN THE NEW
YEAR'S PARADE WITH YOU.

14:16.594 --> 14:18.988
SO YOU NEED TO CHOOSE ONE OF US.

14:24.298 --> 14:25.212
-UM--

14:25.342 --> 14:27.083
I-- UH-- UH--

14:28.476 --> 14:29.564
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

14:29.694 --> 14:30.521
HOBIE!

14:30.652 --> 14:32.132
HOBIE!

14:32.697 --> 14:34.917
-ISN'T HE JUST A
LIVING DOLL, GIRLS?

14:41.837 --> 14:44.274
-I SUPPOSE ASKING
YOU FOR AN EXPLANATION

14:44.405 --> 14:45.928
WOULD BE KIND OF DULL

14:46.059 --> 14:47.190
COMPARED TO WHAT THE TWO OF YOU

14:47.321 --> 14:49.062
HAVE REALLY BEEN UP TO?

14:49.192 --> 14:50.977
-I WAS TRYING TO MAKE MONEY
TO BAIL MY MOM OUT OF JAIL.

14:51.673 --> 14:52.979
-I WAS TRYING TO MAKE MONEY

14:53.109 --> 14:54.502
TO BUY YOU A CHRISTMAS PRESENT.

14:54.632 --> 14:56.112
YOU WANTED THAT NEW
CAMERA LENS SO BAD,

14:56.243 --> 14:57.853
I KNEW YOU WOULDN'T
GET IT FOR YOURSELF.

15:01.509 --> 15:02.727
-ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,

15:02.858 --> 15:04.251
BOTH OF YOU HAD GOOD INTENTIONS

15:04.381 --> 15:06.035
TO DO SOMETHING NICE
FOR YOUR PARENTS,

15:06.166 --> 15:08.908
BUT, GUYS, THE WAY YOU
WENT ABOUT IT WAS LOUSY.

15:09.038 --> 15:10.083
-IT WAS MY IDEA.

15:11.127 --> 15:12.172
-WHY DID I KNOW THAT?

15:14.522 --> 15:16.480
ALL RIGHT.
GO OUT THERE AND APOLOGIZE

15:16.611 --> 15:18.569
AND JUST GIVE THEM ALL
THEIR MONEY BACK, OKAY?

15:19.222 --> 15:20.745
-ABOUT THAT, UH...

15:20.876 --> 15:22.399
WE KIND OF...

15:22.530 --> 15:23.574
DROPPED IT OFF THE PIER.

15:24.227 --> 15:26.534
-YOU KIND OF DROPPED
IT OFF THE PIER.

15:26.664 --> 15:28.101
LIFE IS A BEAUTIFUL THING.

15:28.884 --> 15:30.059
-OKAY.

15:30.799 --> 15:33.149
HOW ARE WE GONNA
RESOLVE THIS ONE?

15:33.889 --> 15:36.239
-I DON'T SUPPOSE
YOU WANT TO RIDE
IN THE NEW YEAR'S PARADE?

15:36.848 --> 15:37.937
-NO.

15:55.171 --> 15:56.520
-HELLO!

15:56.651 --> 15:57.695
HOW'S IT GOING?

15:58.870 --> 15:59.784
-TRACY: GOOD!

16:05.790 --> 16:07.270
-WHAT'S THAT?

16:07.401 --> 16:08.880
-IT'S AN INVITATION
TO A CHRISTMAS PARTY.

16:09.011 --> 16:10.186
-OH!

16:13.233 --> 16:15.278
WELL, WAIT A MINUTE,
I DIDN'T GET ONE.

16:15.409 --> 16:17.411
-YOU WON'T BE GETTING ONE.

16:17.541 --> 16:19.152
THIS IS A PRIVATE PARTY.

16:19.761 --> 16:20.805
FOR TWO.

16:21.458 --> 16:22.938
-HOW ROMANTIC.

16:47.093 --> 16:48.746
-BEAUTIFUL, ISN'T IT?

16:50.487 --> 16:52.141
-I CAN'T TELL YOU
HOW MUCH I APPRECIATE

16:52.272 --> 16:53.360
YOUR COMMITMENT TO
GIVING THESE CHILDREN

16:53.490 --> 16:54.622
A CHRISTMAS, C.J.

16:55.449 --> 16:57.146
-THAT'S WHAT CHRISTMAS
IS ALL ABOUT TO ME.

16:58.365 --> 16:59.496
YOU KNOW, WE MAKE A GOOD TEAM.

17:00.584 --> 17:01.846
IT MUST'VE TAKEN A
LOT OF COMMITMENT

17:01.977 --> 17:03.065
TO JOIN THE PRIESTHOOD.
-HMM.

17:03.196 --> 17:04.806
I USED TO THINK SO, TOO.

17:04.935 --> 17:07.026
BUT I'VE BEEN HAVING
DOUBTS FOR SOME TIME NOW.

17:08.679 --> 17:10.029
-ABOUT BEING A PRIEST?

17:10.855 --> 17:11.943
-THERE'S ONLY ONE GOOD REASON

17:12.074 --> 17:13.336
TO JOIN THE PRIESTHOOD, C.J.,

17:13.467 --> 17:14.816
YET THERE SEEMS TO BE

17:14.945 --> 17:16.425
SO MANY DIFFERENT
REASONS FOR LEAVING.

17:22.301 --> 17:24.304
SOME PRIESTS LOSE
THEIR MOTIVATION,

17:24.434 --> 17:26.522
SOME DOUBT THEIR DEVOTION,

17:26.654 --> 17:29.265
SOME WANT A DIFFERENT LIFESTYLE.

17:30.266 --> 17:31.572
SOME EVEN FALL IN LOVE.

17:34.314 --> 17:36.707
I SHOULDN'T BE BURDENING
YOU WITH MY PROBLEMS.

17:37.230 --> 17:38.318
-DON'T BE SILLY.

17:39.014 --> 17:40.146
I'LL BE THE FIRST
ONE ON MY BLOCK

17:40.276 --> 17:41.973
TO HAVE A PRIEST CONFESS TO ME.

17:43.627 --> 17:44.454
-I'VE GOTTA RUN.

17:44.585 --> 17:46.021
THANKS FOR LISTENING,

17:46.152 --> 17:48.284
AND I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

18:14.658 --> 18:19.098
-[ROMANTIC MUSIC]

18:23.145 --> 18:25.800
-♪ I NEVER FELT

18:25.930 --> 18:30.326
♪ THE TRUE JOY OF CHRISTMAS

18:31.719 --> 18:34.591
♪ MY HEART HAS BEEN HELD

18:34.722 --> 18:38.856
♪ BUT THIS TIME IS DIFFERENT

18:40.162 --> 18:42.208
♪ YOU'RE JUST WHAT I WANTED

18:42.338 --> 18:43.426
-MAY I HAVE THIS DANCE?

18:44.732 --> 18:46.255
-YOU MAY INDEED, SIR.

18:48.866 --> 18:54.089
♪ I'M SPENDING THIS CHRISTMAS IN LOVE

18:57.266 --> 19:00.356
-♪ I'VE BEEN ROUND THE WORD

19:00.487 --> 19:04.926
♪ SEEN ALL KINDS OF LONELY

19:06.188 --> 19:08.669
♪ LIVED AND I'VE LEARNED

19:08.799 --> 19:12.934
♪ WISHING SOMEONE WOULD HOLD ME

19:14.631 --> 19:17.243
♪ 'VE SPENT ENOUGH TIME

19:17.373 --> 19:22.161
♪ CHASING STARS UP ABOVE

19:23.074 --> 19:28.341
♪ I'M SPENDING THIS CHRISTMAS IN LOVE

19:31.909 --> 19:34.651
♪ DANCING WITH YOU

19:35.478 --> 19:38.655
♪ BY THE LIGHT OF THE MOON

19:40.527 --> 19:45.706
♪ IT'S LIKE A DREAM COME TRUE

19:49.057 --> 19:52.321
♪ IN YOUR EMBRACE

19:53.366 --> 19:56.238
♪ I'VE FOUND MY PLACE

19:57.718 --> 20:02.288
♪ IT'S ALL BECAUSE OF YOU

20:10.513 --> 20:12.907
♪ NOW WE'RE TOGETHER

20:13.037 --> 20:16.737
♪ AND MY HEART HAS A HOME

20:19.087 --> 20:23.352
♪ I WON'T SPEND ANOTHER SILENT NIGHT

20:23.483 --> 20:26.181
♪ ALL ALONE

20:27.704 --> 20:30.272
♪ HOLDING YOU CLOSE

20:30.403 --> 20:34.885
♪ I JUST CAN'T GET ENOUGH

20:35.712 --> 20:38.976
♪ I'M SPENDING THIS CHRISTMAS ♪

20:39.107 --> 20:41.196
-HEY, HEY, HEY.

20:42.806 --> 20:44.330
WHAT'S ALL THIS?

20:45.244 --> 20:47.246
-IT'S BEEN SO LONG
SINCE I CRIED A TEAR

20:47.376 --> 20:49.552
OF PURE AND ABSOLUTE HAPPINESS.

20:53.077 --> 20:55.428
-YOU KNOW I'M FALLING IN
LOVE WITH YOU, DON'T YOU?

21:22.977 --> 21:23.760
-C.J.: MITCH.

21:23.891 --> 21:24.674
-MITCH: HEY!

21:24.805 --> 21:25.588
-CAN WE TALK?

21:25.719 --> 21:27.068
I NEED YOUR ADVICE.

21:27.198 --> 21:28.983
-AH, CAN YOU MAKE
IT REAL QUICK?

21:29.113 --> 21:30.332
I'VE GOT SOME SHOPPING AND OH,

21:30.463 --> 21:32.160
ONE SURFING DAY
LEFT 'TIL CHRISTMAS.

21:32.291 --> 21:33.248
-THAT'S OKAY.

21:33.379 --> 21:34.902
YOU WOULDN'T UNDERSTAND, ANYWAY.

21:36.425 --> 21:38.035
-C.J., WAIT A SECOND.

21:38.166 --> 21:39.428
YOU CAN TALK TO ME.

21:39.559 --> 21:41.038
COME ON.

21:41.169 --> 21:42.997
NO MATTER WHAT PROBLEM
YOU'VE EVER HAD,

21:43.127 --> 21:46.435
LIFEGUARDING, MEN, MONEY, MEN.

21:46.566 --> 21:48.481
YOU KNOW I'VE ALWAYS UNDERSTOOD.

21:48.611 --> 21:50.744
AND I'VE NEVER
JUDGED YOU, HAVE I?

21:51.875 --> 21:54.487
-FATHER RYAN TOLD
ME THAT HE'S THINKING

21:54.617 --> 21:55.792
OF LEAVING THE PRIESTHOOD.

21:56.880 --> 22:01.189
AND I'M AFRAID IT'S BECAUSE
HE'S FALLEN IN LOVE WITH ME.

22:10.764 --> 22:11.678
-A PRIEST?

22:11.808 --> 22:12.766
WHY A PRIEST?

22:12.896 --> 22:13.984
YOU COULD HAVE ANY MAN YOU WANT.

22:14.115 --> 22:15.595
MATT ADORES YOU!
BUT A PRIEST?

22:15.725 --> 22:17.248
-MITCH, IT'S NOT
WHAT YOU THINK.

22:17.379 --> 22:19.250
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING TO
ENCOURAGE FATHER RYAN.

22:19.381 --> 22:21.252
I DID NOTHING TO BE ASHAMED OF.

22:21.383 --> 22:23.342
THIS IS A TOTAL
MISUNDERSTANDING.

22:23.472 --> 22:24.865
SOME HELP YOU'VE BEEN.

22:24.995 --> 22:26.910
-AH AH WHA-- AH, NOW
THAT'S MORE LIKE IT.

22:27.041 --> 22:27.998
AND YOU DID NOTHING WRONG,

22:28.129 --> 22:29.870
IT WAS A TOTAL MISUNDERSTANDING,

22:30.000 --> 22:32.263
YOU'RE PREPARED TO TAKE ACTION
AND DO SOMETHING ABOUT IT.

22:32.873 --> 22:34.048
YOU'RE IN TOTAL CONTROL.

22:34.178 --> 22:35.789
-YOU'RE RIGHT.

22:35.919 --> 22:37.486
I AM IN CONTROL.

22:37.617 --> 22:39.358
-NOW GO OUT THERE AND
STRAIGHTEN THIS MESS OUT.

22:39.488 --> 22:40.707
-THANKS, MITCH.

22:45.407 --> 22:46.582
-A PRIEST?

22:47.670 --> 22:49.368
IT'S CHRISTMAS!

23:01.902 --> 23:03.033
-IT'S A BEAUTIFUL THING, HUH?

23:04.252 --> 23:05.427
WATCHING KIDS PLAY,

23:06.036 --> 23:07.255
HEARING THEM LAUGH.

23:08.909 --> 23:10.954
SITTIN' ON SANTA'S KNEE.

23:12.347 --> 23:15.524
-I RAISED MY DAUGHTER
NOT TO HAVE FANTASIES
LIKE SANTA CLAUS.

23:16.351 --> 23:18.309
HER FATHER LEFT AND DESTROYED

23:18.440 --> 23:21.138
ANY FAIRY TALE ENDING
FOR BOTH OF US.

23:22.966 --> 23:25.404
-WELL, I CAN UNDERSTAND
YOU NOT WANTING JOEY

23:25.534 --> 23:27.144
TO HAVE A FANTASY LIFE.

23:28.450 --> 23:29.886
DOESN'T SHE DESERVE A REAL ONE?

23:30.713 --> 23:32.019
I MEAN IT'S NOT
MUCH OF A CHRISTMAS

23:32.149 --> 23:33.107
FOR THAT LITTLE GIRL, IS IT?

23:33.237 --> 23:34.674
CONNING PEOPLE OUT OF MONEY?

23:35.283 --> 23:38.112
WORRYING ABOUT BAILING
HER MOTHER OUT OF JAIL?

23:39.026 --> 23:40.593
IT'S ALSO NOT MUCH OF A LIFE.

23:41.376 --> 23:43.117
-I DID A LOT OF THINKING
WHEN I WAS IN JAIL.

23:43.247 --> 23:46.294
I DECIDED I WANTED JOEY TO
HAVE WHAT OTHER CHILDREN HAVE.

23:46.425 --> 23:51.038
A HOME, A DOG, A DINNER TIME.

23:53.127 --> 23:54.781
BUT THESE THINGS
COST MONEY AND...

23:55.434 --> 23:57.174
THAT MEANS A JOB.

23:57.871 --> 23:58.959
-TELL YOU WHAT.

23:59.612 --> 24:00.874
YOU GO TALK TO THE JUDGE,

24:01.527 --> 24:02.832
AND YOU DO WHAT YOU GOTTA DO,

24:03.616 --> 24:05.487
AND I'LL HELP YOU GET A JOB.

24:05.618 --> 24:06.662
-YOU'D DO THAT FOR US?

24:06.793 --> 24:08.185
-TOMORROW'S CHRISTMAS.

24:09.143 --> 24:11.232
I WANT YOU TO GIVE
YOURSELF AND YOUR DAUGHTER

24:11.362 --> 24:12.842
THE BEST PRESENT EVER.

24:13.800 --> 24:15.062
A REAL LIFE.

24:17.020 --> 24:21.721
-[CHILDREN CHATTERING]

24:30.991 --> 24:31.774
-HI.

24:31.905 --> 24:33.254
-C.J.!

24:33.384 --> 24:35.082
I'M GLAD TO FIND
YOU, WE NEED TO TALK.

24:35.604 --> 24:36.605
-LET'S WALK.

24:38.259 --> 24:40.827
-C.J., I'VE MADE A DECISION,

24:40.957 --> 24:42.176
AND I WANT YOU TO
KNOW HOW MUCH I--

24:42.306 --> 24:43.351
-SAM.

24:43.482 --> 24:44.570
FATHER.

24:45.571 --> 24:47.486
I NEED TO SAY SOMETHING.

24:47.616 --> 24:50.010
I CAN'T TELL YOU
HOW FLATTERED I--

24:50.750 --> 24:53.579
I MEAN I REALLY LIKE
YOU AS A FRIEND.

24:54.710 --> 24:57.757
BUT IF YOU'RE THINKING OF
LEAVING THE PRIESTHOOD FOR ME,

24:57.887 --> 25:01.456
I MEAN, YOU PROBABLY ONLY THINK
THAT YOU'RE IN LOVE WITH ME.

25:01.587 --> 25:03.502
I MEAN, I'M IN LOVE WITH MATT,

25:03.632 --> 25:06.069
AND YOU'LL GET OVER ME, I KNOW.

25:06.200 --> 25:07.810
-C.J.,

25:07.941 --> 25:09.464
I'M NOT THINKING OF LEAVING
THE PRIESTHOOD FOR YOU.

25:10.160 --> 25:11.422
-YOU'RE NOT?

25:11.553 --> 25:12.380
-I'M GOING ON A
RETREAT TO FIGURE OUT

25:12.511 --> 25:13.947
WHERE MY HEART IS.

25:14.077 --> 25:15.775
IF I DECIDE TO LEAVE,
IT'LL BE FOR MYSELF.

25:16.427 --> 25:17.472
-BUT THE THINGS YOU SAID!

25:17.603 --> 25:18.908
OH, I'M SO EMBARRASSED.

25:19.039 --> 25:20.170
-[LAUGHING]

25:20.301 --> 25:21.737
-C.J., I'M SO SORRY.

25:21.868 --> 25:23.913
I'VE BEEN SO WRAPPED UP
WITH MY OWN PROBLEMS.

25:24.566 --> 25:27.177
YOU'RE A BEAUTIFUL,
CHARMING AND LOVING WOMAN

25:27.308 --> 25:28.962
BUT THAT HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH MY CHOICE.

25:29.745 --> 25:31.965
I WANTED TO TALK TO YOU TO
TELL YOU THAT I'D BE LEAVING,

25:32.095 --> 25:34.184
BUT THAT SOMEONE WILL BE
TAKING MY PLACE AT ST. FRANCIS

25:34.315 --> 25:35.838
WHILE I GO ON THE RETREAT.

25:36.796 --> 25:38.319
I REALLY NEED TO
MAKE A DECISION,

25:38.449 --> 25:40.147
AND I HOPE YOU'LL UNDERSTAND.

25:40.277 --> 25:42.279
-OH, I DO. I DO UNDERSTAND.

25:42.410 --> 25:44.586
FINALLY.
-WORKING WITH YOU
AND THE CHILDREN

25:44.717 --> 25:46.457
HAS BEEN A WONDERFUL EXPERIENCE.

25:47.589 --> 25:49.330
I ONCE TOLD YOU THAT I ENVY YOU.

25:49.460 --> 25:51.201
I DO.

25:51.332 --> 25:54.204
I ENVY YOUR TOTAL COMMITMENT
AND PASSION FOR YOUR WORK.

25:54.901 --> 25:56.206
I'M GONNA MISS YOU.

25:57.338 --> 25:58.600
-I'M GONNA MISS YOU, TOO.

25:58.731 --> 26:00.515
-NOT ENOUGH.

26:00.646 --> 26:02.473
YOU'RE REALLY GONNA LIKE THE
PRIEST THAT'S TAKING MY PLACE.

26:02.604 --> 26:04.650
TALL, BLOND SURFER TYPE.

26:04.780 --> 26:07.043
-[LAUGHING]

26:07.174 --> 26:08.697
-WELL YOU'RE GONNA STAY
FOR CHRISTMAS, WON'T YOU?

26:08.828 --> 26:10.177
-OH, I WOULDN'T MISS IT.

26:11.308 --> 26:13.789
THE SEA IS SIMPLY GLORIOUS!

26:13.920 --> 26:18.620
-[CHRISTMAS MUSIC]

26:24.583 --> 26:27.411
-[GRUNTING]

26:30.458 --> 26:31.415
-GEEZ!

26:31.546 --> 26:32.982
MATT!

26:33.113 --> 26:34.418
-BENNY.

26:34.549 --> 26:35.637
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
HERE AT THIS HOUR?

26:35.768 --> 26:37.900
-UH, STRAIGHTENING UP.

26:38.553 --> 26:39.423
YOU GUYS ARE SLOBS,
YOU KNOW THAT?

26:39.554 --> 26:40.990
-MM-HMM.

26:41.121 --> 26:43.036
EXCUSE ME, BENNY, I NEED
TO GET IN THE CLOSET.

26:43.166 --> 26:44.167
-NO YOU DON'T.

26:44.298 --> 26:45.473
-YES, I DO.

26:45.604 --> 26:46.996
-MATT, THERE'S A
HUGE DOG IN THERE.

26:47.127 --> 26:48.432
[HOWLING]

26:49.782 --> 26:51.087
-BENNY.

26:51.218 --> 26:52.132
-IT'S ONE OF THEM
LITTLE NASTY DOGS.

26:52.262 --> 26:53.655
[YAPPING]

26:54.221 --> 26:55.831
-NOW.

26:55.962 --> 26:59.139
-UM, A LITTLE TEENY--
WOOF. WOOF.
-NOW!

27:13.806 --> 27:16.156
ALL US GUYS WANTED TO DO
SOMETHING SPECIAL FOR THE KIDS.

27:16.286 --> 27:17.897
WE DIDN'T WANT YOU
TO KNOW IT WAS US.

27:18.027 --> 27:20.464
-BENNY, DID-- DID YOU
GUYS DECORATE MY TOWER

27:20.595 --> 27:22.162
AND LEAVE ME THE CHRISTMAS TREE?

27:22.292 --> 27:23.467
-YOU SAVED MY LIFE, MATT.

27:25.644 --> 27:27.471
I WANTED TO DO SOMETHING
SPECIAL FOR YOU, TOO.

27:30.518 --> 27:31.432
WHAT?

27:32.738 --> 27:33.869
-I JUST THOUGHT
THAT YOU WERE LIKE,

27:34.000 --> 27:35.610
SANTA'S HELPERS, YOU KNOW?

27:35.741 --> 27:37.003
ELVES.

27:38.004 --> 27:38.918
-WE ARE.

27:46.099 --> 27:49.885
-[FESTIVE MUSIC]

27:51.844 --> 27:54.716
-[WHISTLING]

27:54.847 --> 27:56.022
-HEY, MITCH!

27:56.152 --> 27:57.240
-MITCH: YO!
-I NEED A WITNESS.

27:57.371 --> 27:58.764
-WHAT'S GOING ON?

27:58.894 --> 28:01.157
-BENNY, TELL MITCH
WHAT YOU JUST TOLD ME.

28:01.897 --> 28:02.855
-[SIGHING]

28:02.985 --> 28:04.204
I CAN'T HIDE IT ANY LONGER.

28:04.857 --> 28:06.249
I'M ONE OF SANTA'S HELPERS.

28:06.380 --> 28:08.208
-[LAUGHING]

28:08.338 --> 28:10.036
-HAS EVERYONE LOST
IT AROUND HERE?

28:10.166 --> 28:12.081
I MEAN IT'S NOT BAD ENOUGH
THAT HE THINKS HE'S AN ELF,

28:12.212 --> 28:14.257
BUT YOU ACTUALLY BELIEVE HIM.

28:14.388 --> 28:15.563
-WELL, I, UH--

28:15.694 --> 28:16.869
-BUT I AM ONE OF
SANTA'S HELPERS.

28:16.999 --> 28:18.000
I AM AN ELF!

28:18.131 --> 28:19.001
-OKAY.

28:19.132 --> 28:20.046
YOU'RE AN ELF.

28:20.176 --> 28:21.482
I MEAN, WHO AM I TO DOUBT?

28:21.612 --> 28:23.658
COME ON, I MEAN,
PARASAILING SANTAS,

28:23.789 --> 28:25.878
A PRIEST IS IN LOVE WITH C.J.,

28:26.008 --> 28:27.793
I MEAN, NEW YEAR'S
DAY PARADES, WOW!

28:27.923 --> 28:29.708
HEY, SAY HELLO TO THE BIG GUY.

28:30.752 --> 28:33.102
HO HO HO. WHOA!

28:34.843 --> 28:35.975
-GOTTA GO, MATT.

28:36.105 --> 28:37.324
BIG NIGHT, YA KNOW.

28:39.239 --> 28:40.501
GOT A LOT TO DO.

28:41.763 --> 28:42.590
OH YEAH, MATT?

28:42.721 --> 28:43.765
-YEAH?

28:44.592 --> 28:45.549
-GOTCHA!

28:45.680 --> 28:46.812
-[LAUGHING]

28:55.298 --> 28:57.300
-[CHATTERING]

28:57.431 --> 28:58.737
-COULD YOU PLEASE GO OUTSIDE

28:58.867 --> 28:59.999
AND PUT THAT ON THE
CHRISTMAS TRUCK?

29:00.129 --> 29:00.956
THANKS.

29:04.351 --> 29:05.395
-MERRY CHRISTMAS.

29:08.007 --> 29:08.877
HEY.

29:09.486 --> 29:10.661
ARE YOU BEHAVING YOURSELVES?

29:10.792 --> 29:12.098
-YES, WE'RE BEHAVING AS ELVES.

29:12.228 --> 29:13.055
-CAROLINE: MITCH!

29:13.186 --> 29:14.187
-[LAUGHING]

29:14.317 --> 29:15.318
-WE HAVE A HUGE PROBLEM,

29:15.449 --> 29:16.450
THEY DON'T HAVE ONE AVAILABLE.

29:20.280 --> 29:21.890
-ARE YOU SURE?

29:22.021 --> 29:22.978
-YEAH, THEY SAID THE EARLIEST
THEY COULD GET ONE HERE

29:23.109 --> 29:24.632
WOULD BE LATE THIS AFTERNOON.

29:24.763 --> 29:25.851
-WELL, THEN THE ONLY
SURPRISE WE GOT GOING HERE

29:25.981 --> 29:26.895
IS THAT THERE'S NO SURPRISE.

29:27.026 --> 29:29.202
-[GROANING]

29:30.464 --> 29:31.552
-SORRY!

29:32.901 --> 29:33.815
-OKAY.
-CONTACT LENS!

29:33.946 --> 29:34.860
NOBODY MOVE!

29:35.599 --> 29:37.645
-WHAT? WHAT IS IT?

29:39.038 --> 29:40.604
HELLO?

29:40.735 --> 29:43.042
-I'M SORRY, WE DIDN'T
MEAN TO BE ELVESDROPPPING.

29:43.172 --> 29:44.478
EAVESDROPPING.

29:47.263 --> 29:49.004
WE HEARD YOU TALKING
ABOUT A SURPRISE.

29:49.135 --> 29:50.136
PERHAPS WE COULD
BE OF ASSISTANCE.

29:50.266 --> 29:51.746
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

29:51.877 --> 29:54.227
-UH, CAROLINE, I WOULD
LIKE TO INTRODUCE TO YOU,

29:54.357 --> 29:55.881
BENNY THE ELF.

29:56.751 --> 29:57.970
-YOU'RE KIDDING, RIGHT?

29:58.100 --> 30:00.102
-ABOUT SOME THINGS
WE DON'T KID,

30:00.668 --> 30:02.148
AND WHEN IT COMES TO
CHRISTMAS SURPRISES,

30:02.278 --> 30:03.889
WELL, WE CAN'T BE BEAT.

30:04.672 --> 30:06.108
AND WE WOULD BE HONORED

30:06.239 --> 30:07.893
TO HELP YOU SURPRISE
YOUR BEAUTIFUL LADY.

30:08.023 --> 30:10.112
-WAIT A MINUTE, I NEVER SAID
WHO THE SURPRISE WAS FOR.

30:10.721 --> 30:12.506
-AND NOBODY ELSE KNEW ABOUT IT.

30:14.247 --> 30:15.509
-LET'S TALK TURKEY.

30:15.639 --> 30:16.684
COME HERE.

30:22.255 --> 30:23.169
-OKAY.

30:25.562 --> 30:27.608
WATCH OUT!
[LAUGHING]

30:34.180 --> 30:35.790
ARE YOU READY FOR YOUR SURPRISE?

30:35.921 --> 30:38.053
-IF I HAVE TO STAND HERE
ANOTHER MOMENT LIKE THIS,

30:38.184 --> 30:39.881
I ASSURE YOU I WILL BURST.

30:47.933 --> 30:50.109
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.
IT'S SNOWING!

30:50.239 --> 30:51.850
-MERRY WHITE CHRISTMAS!

30:51.980 --> 30:52.763
-OH!

30:52.894 --> 30:53.764
-MMM.

30:58.465 --> 30:59.945
COME ON, COME ON.

31:00.946 --> 31:05.776
-[FESTIVE MUSIC]

31:09.606 --> 31:11.739
-[LAUGHING]

31:29.844 --> 31:33.543
-♪ EVERYDAY IS CHRISTMAS
WHEN I'M WITH YOU ♪

31:33.674 --> 31:38.897
♪ YOU'RE THE JOY, YOU'RE THE PEACE,
YOU'RE THE GIFT UNDER THE TREE YEAH ♪

